{
 "name": "RPlog_Storm_Front",
 "title": "Storm Front",
 "summary": "On a rain-lashed landing pad in Central City on Athaniss, the reborn Sith lord Darth Malus is drawn to a newly arrived ship and the cloaked Falleen woman who disembarks from it, Ssanyu Natrulon. Sensing her as maddeningly familiar, Malus follows and presses her, and she reveals herself as 'the Faceless,' the herald who announced his return to the galaxy. Retiring aboard his freighter the Revenant, the two former intelligence directors spend the evening fencing over caf and Corellian whiskey, probing each other's motives, histories, and the immunities of her species to Force manipulation. Malus diagnoses her as a powerful, purposeless tool seeking renewed purpose, while Ssanyu refuses to become anyone's pawn and insists on neutrality between Malus and her longtime arrangement with Vichten. They part with a guarded accord, Malus asking her to carry an offer of parley to Vassily Korolov and hinting at deeper games to come, as he must flee Athaniss ahead of the Imperium bounty on his head.",
